f>{{cite web|title=Tracy McGrady, Bill Self, Rebecca Lobo and Muffet McGraw Headline Class|url=http://www.hoophall.com/news/naismith-memorial-basketball-hall-of-fame-class-of-2017-announcement-presented-by-haggar-clothing-company/|publisher=Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame Official Website|accessdate=April 29, 2017}}</ref>\n* '''2\u00d7 [[NBA annual scoring champion|NBA scoring champion]]''': 2003, 2004\n* '''7\u00d7 [[NBA All-Star Game|NBA All-Star]]''': 2001, 2002, 2003, 2004, 2005, 2006, 2007\n* '''7\u00d7 [[All-NBA Team|All-NBA]]''':\n:* '''First Team''': 2002, 2003\n:* '''Second Team''': 2001, 2004, 2007\n:* '''Third Team''': 2005, 2008\n* '''[[NBA Most Improved Player Award]]''': 2001\n* '''[[2003 Tournament of the Americas|Tournament of the Americas Gold Medalist]]''': 2003<ref>{{cite web|title=Men's Tournament of the Americas -- 2003|url=https://www.usab.com/history/national-team-mens/mens-tournament-of-the-americas-2003.aspx|publisher=USA Basketball Official Website|accessdate=April 29, 2017}}</ref>\n* '''[[Chinese Basketball Association|CBA]] All-Star''': 2013\n* '''No. 1 retired''' by [[Qingdao Eagles|Qingdao DoubleStar Eagles]]: 2015\n* '''[[Mr. Basketball USA]]''': 1997<ref>{{cite web|last1=Flores|first1=Ronnie|title=Mr. Basketball USA Tracker week 8|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/high-school/boys-basketball/post/_/id/3506/mr-basketball-usa-tracker-week-8|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref>\n* '''[[McDonald's All-American]]''': 1997\n\n===Orlando Magic franchise records===\n* '''Most points in a game''' with 62 (March 10, 2004 vs. [[Washington Wizards]])<ref>{{cite web|title=T-Mac Tees Off for 62 Points in Magic Win|url=http://www.nba.com/games/20040310/WASORL/recap.html|publisher=NBA Official Website|accessdate=April 29, 2017}}</ref>\n* '''Most field goal attempts in a season''' with 1813 (2002\u201303)<ref name=\"Season Leaders\">{{cite web|title=Orlando Magic Season Leaders|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/teams/ORL/leaders_season.html|publisher=Basketball Reference|accessdate=April 29, 2017}}</ref>\n* '''Most free throws made in a season''' with 576 (2002\u201303)<ref name=\"Season Leaders\" />\n* '''Most points in a season''' with 2407 (2002\u201303)<ref name=\"Season Leaders\" />\n* '''Highest minutes per game in a season''' with 40.1 (2002\u201303)<ref name=\"Season Leaders\" />\n* '''Highest points per game in a season''' with 32.1 (2002\u201303)<ref name=\"Season Leaders\" />\n* '''Highest minutes per game in a career''' with 39.4<ref name=\"Career Leaders\">{{cite web|title=Orlanda Magic Career Leaders|url=https://www.basketball-reference.com/teams/ORL/leaders_career.html|publisher=Basketball Reference|accessdate=April 29, 2017}}</ref>\n* '''Highest points per game in a career''' with 28.1<ref name=\"Career Leaders\" />\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Sports}}\n* [[List of individual National Basketball Association scoring leaders by season]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association players with 60 or more points in a game]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Tracy McGrady}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20041211112334/http://www.t-mac.com/ Tracy McGrady's Official Website]\n* [http://stats.nba.com/playerProfile.html?PlayerID=1503 Career statistics and player information from NBA.com]\n* {{basketballstats|bbr=m/mcgratr01}}\n* {{baseballstats|brm=mcgrad000tra}}\n* [http://cbadata.sports.sohu.com/players/statistics/501553 Chinese Basketball Association Official Profile And Stats] {{in lang|zh}}\n* {{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/basketball/2013/09/13/tracy_mcgrady_wishes_he_had_stayed_in_toronto_feschuk.html|title=Tracy McGrady wishes he had stayed in Toronto: Feschuk|last=Feschuk|first=Dave|newspaper=[[Toronto Star]]|date=September 13, 2013|accessdate=September 14, 2013}}\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{Mr. Basketball USA}}\n{{USA Today National Basketball Player of the Year}}\n{{1997 NBA Draft}}\n{{NBA Most Improved Players}}\n