uture of work/[[unemployment]]\n#[[Climate change]]\n#[[Financial crisis of 2007\u20132008]]\n#Future of the internet/[[Fourth Industrial Revolution]]\n#[[Gender equality]]\n#[[Global trade]] and investment and [[regulatory]] frameworks\n#Long-term [[investment]]/[[Investment strategy]]\n#Future [[healthcare]]\n{{see also|sustainable growth|green economy|global recession|International Monetary Fund|World Trade Organization}}\n\n== Global environmental issues==\n{{main|List of environmental issues}}\n\nNo single issue can be analysed, treated, or isolated from the others.<ref>http://www.geni.org/globalenergy/issues/global/major-global-issues-diagram-lg.jpg</ref> For example, [[habitat loss]] and climate change adversely affect biodiversity. Deforestation and pollution are direct consequences of overpopulation and both, in turn, affect biodiversity. While overpopulation locally leads to [[rural flight]], this is more than counterbalanced by accelerating [[urbanization]] and urban sprawl. Theories like the [[World-systems theory|world-system theory]] and the [[Gaia hypothesis]] focus on the inter-dependency aspect of environmental and economic issues. Among the most evident environmental problems are:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conserve-energy-future.com/15-current-environmental-problems.php|title=15 Current Environmental Problems That Our World is Facing - Conserve Energy Future|first=|last=Rinkesh|date=27 June 2014|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://inhabitat.com/why-we-need-earth-day-7-most-pressing-environmental-problems-we-need-to-solve/|title=The World's 6 Most Pressing Environmental Issues|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrdc.org/issues/|title=NRDC - Our Work|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalissues.org/issue/168/environmental-issues|title=Environmental Issues \u2014 Global Issues|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n*[[Overconsumption]] &ndash; situation where resource use has outpaced the sustainable capacity of the ecosystem. This, along with [[overpopulation]], are the primary factors affecting the severity of all of the rest of the issues on this list.\n*[[Overpopulation]] &ndash; too many people for the planet to sustain. This, along with [[overconsumption]], are the primary factors affecting the severity of all of the rest of the issues on this list.\n*[[Acid rain]]\n*[[Biodiversity loss]]\n*[[Deforestation]]\n*[[Desertification]]\n*[[Global warming]]/[[climate change]]\n*[[Habitat destruction]]\n*[[Holocene extinction]]\n*[[Ocean acidification]]\n*[[Ozone layer depletion]]\n*[[Pollution]]\n**[[Waste]] and [[waste disposal]]\n**[[Water pollution]]\n*[[Resource depletion]]\n*[[Urban sprawl]]\n\n{{see also|zero population growth|green economy}}\n\n==See also==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=15em|\n*[[Center for Global Food Issues]]\n*[[Chicago Council on Global Affairs]]\n*[[Climate change]]\n*[[Cybersecurity]]\n*[[Developing country]]\n*[[Earth Economics]]\n*[[Earth system science]]\n*[[Ecological footprint]]\n*[[Energy crisis]]\n*[[Environmental social science]]\n*[[Financial crisis]]\n*[[Global catastrophic risk]]\n*[[Global Challenges Foundation]]\n*[[Global change]]\n*[[Global governance]]\n*[[Global health]]\n**[[Antimicrobial resistance]]\n*[[Global justice]]\n*[[Global Rights]]\n*[[Global warming controversy]]\n*[[Human impact on the environment]]\n*[[Human security]]\n*[[Intergovernmental organization]]\n*[[List of United Nations peacekeeping missions]]\n*[[Liu Institute for Global Issues]]\n*[[Mass surveillance]]\n*[[Ozone depletion and climate change]]\n*[[Pandemic]]\n*[[Peak oil]]\n*[[Social justice]]\n*[[Species extinction]]\n*[[Washington consensus]]\n*[[World Community Grid]]\n*[[World-systems theory]]\n*[[World War]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Literature==\n*{{cite book\n|title=Global Issues\n|author=John L. Seitz, Kristen A. Hite\n|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell\n|edition=4\n|year=2012\n|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=KYLtrTw5UMYC&printsec=frontcover&dq=isbn:9780470655641&hl=de&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|isbn=978-0-470-65564-1}}\n*{{cite book\n|title=Global Issues\n|edition= 4th\n|author=Richard J. Payne\n|publisher=Pearson\n|year=2012\n|isbn=978-0205854592\n}}\n*{{cite book\n|title=Introducing Global Issues\n|edition=5th\n|editor=Michael T. Snarr, D. Neil Snarr\n|publisher=Lynne Rienner Pub\n|year=2012\n|isbn=978-1588268457\n}}\n*{{cite book\n|title=Global Issues: A Cross-Cultural Perspective Paperback\n|year=2013\n|author=Shirley A. Fedorak\n|isbn=978-1442605961\n}}\n*''[[Global Education Magazine]]''\n*''[[Global Environmental Politics]]''\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Globalization issues}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://dus.psu.edu/global/learn/|title=Think Global: Learn More About Global Issues|website=dus.psu.edu|language=en|access-date=2018-01-31}}\n*{{cite web | title=Global issues | website=TED.com | date=2016-05-11 | url=https://www.ted.com/topics/global+issues | ref={{sfnref | TED.com | 2016}} | access-date=2018-01-18}}\n*{{cite web | title=Global Issues | website=TakingITGlobal | url=https://www.tigweb.org/global-issues/ | ref={{sfnref | TakingITGlobal}} | access-date=2018-01-18}}\n*{{cite web | title=Global Issues : social, political, economic and environmental issues that affect us all | website=Global Issues | date=2011-09-24 | url=http://globalissues.org | ref={{sfnref | Global Issues | 2011}} | access-date=2018-01-18}}\n*{{cite web | title=Global Issues Network | website=Global Issues Network | date=2013-03-28 | url=http://globalissuesnetwork.org | ref={{sfnref | Global Issues Network | 2013}} | access-date=2018-01-18}}\n*{{cite web | title=Issues of resilience, interdependence and growth affect global climate change risk | website=Carbon Brief | date=2014-02-20 | url=https://www.carbonbrief.org/issues-of-resilience-interdependence-and-growth-affect-global-climate-change-risk | ref={{sfnref | Carbon Brief | 2014}} | access-date=2018-01-18}}\n*{{cite web | title=A list of the most urgent global issues | website=80,000 Hours | date=2017-04-30 | url=https://80000hours.org/articles/cause-selection/ | ref={{sfnref | 80,000 Hours | 2017}} | access-date=2018-06-06}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Politics|Society}}\n\n{{Human impact on the environment}}\n\n[[Category:Global issues| ]]\n[[Category:Global inequality]]\n[[Category:Lists of environmental organizations|Global]]\n", "name_user": "104.12.77.210", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eHeading text)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_global_issues"}
{"title_page": "Roberto Burioni", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian doctor known for his strong stand against the antivaccination movement.}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name           = Roberto Burioni\n| image          = Roberto Burioni 2017.jpg\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1962|12|10}}\n| birth_place    = [[Pesaro]], Italy\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| alma_mater     = [[Universit\u00e0 Cattolica del Sacro Cuore]] <small>(Graduation)</small><br>[[University of Genoa]] <small>(PhD)</small>\n| occupation     = [[Medical Doctor]], [[University professor]]\n| spouse         = married\n| children       = 1 daughter\n}}\n\n'''Roberto Burioni''' (born 10 December 1962) is an Italian physician and Professor of [[Microbiology]] and [[Virology]] at the [[Vita-Salute San Raffaele University]], [[Milan]] where he runs a lab developing human monoclonal antibodies against human infectious agents, the study of pathogen-host interplay, and the use of molecular tools in the early diagnosis of infectious diseases.{{R|\"History\"}} Burioni has risen to fame in Italy for his strong stance against the [[antivaccination]] movement.{{R|\"ScienceMag\"}}\n\n== Education, career, and activism ==\n\n=== 1980s to 2004: studies and early career ===\nAfter graduating from the Liceo Classico Raffaello, [[Urbino]], [[Italy]], he received his Medical Degree from the [[Universit\u00e0 Cattolica del Sacro Cuore]] Medical School in Rome and a [[Ph.D.]] in Microbiological Sciences from the [[University of Genoa]].\n\nBurioni attended the Center for Disease Control in Atlanta, Georgia and the Wistar Institute of the University of Pennsylvania as a visiting student in the laboratory of Dr. [[Hilary Koprowski]] and [[Carlo M. Croce|Carlo Maria Croce]]. He has been a visiting scientist at both the Center for Molecular Genetics at the [[University of California]], [[San Diego]], and at the [[Scripps Research Institute]].\n\nHe was appointed Assistant Professor at the Medical School of the [[Universit\u00e0 Cattolica del Sacro Cuore]], [[Rome]], in 1995 before moving to Assistant Professor in Virology at the Medical School of the [[University of Ancona]] in 1999.\nBurioni moved to the medical school at the [[Vita-Salute San Raffaele University| Universit\u00e0 Vita-Salute San Raffaele]] in Milan in 2004, first as an Associate Professor and later as Full Professor of Microbiology and Virology.{{R|\"History\"}}\n\n=== 2016 to present day: stand against the antivaccination movement and continuous career ===\nBurioni is an active campaigner against the [[antivaccination]] movement and rose to fame in Italy after an appearance on the TV talk show \"Virus\" in 2016, on the national TV channel [[Rai 2]].{{R|\"ScienceMag\"}} The majority of the segment was given to Red Ronnie, a DJ, and former actress [[Eleonora Brigliadori]], both of whom hold antivaccination positions. Burioni was left with only a few minutes in which to rebut the misinformation. In response, Burioni posted to [[Facebook]] giving his version of the facts. The post was read by over 5 million people in one day. The TV show \"Virus\" was eventually canceled at the end of the season.{{R|\"FalseBalance\"}} Since then he has developed a large following on social media with almost 480,000 followers on Facebook{{R|\"ScienceMag\"}} and over 114,000 followers on [[Twitter]].{{R|\"Twitter\"}}\n\nIn 2017 he authored the book \"Il vaccino non \u00e8 un'opinione: Le vaccinazioni spiegate a chi proprio non le vuole capire\" (\"The vaccine is not an opinion: Vaccinations, explained to those who just do not want to understand them\"){{R|\"Amazon\"}} which won the 2017 Premio Asimov ([[Isaac Asimov Awards|Asimov Award]]), an annual award established by the [[Gran Sasso Science Institute]] of [[L'Aquila]] awarded to books of science dissemination published in Italy during the previous year.{{R|\"ResearchItaly\"|\"LinkedIn\"}}\n\nIn 2018 Burioni, along with several colleagues, created the website Medical Facts. Articles on the site are written by [[Biomedical scientist|medical scientists]], doctors and other [[Health professional|health professionals]] with the intent of promoting news and advice on a range of health issues.{{R|\"ScienceMag\"|\"MedicalFacts\"}}\n\nIn January 2019 Burioni launched a Pact for Science, calling on all Italian political parties to sign on and pledge to follow five points: to support science as a universal value of progress and humanity; to refuse to support or tolerate pseudoscience, pseudomedicine, and any treatments that are not based on scientific and medical evidence; to prevent pseudo-scientists from creating unjustified alarm regarding health care interventions which have been scientifically and medically demonstrated to be safe; to implement programs designed to correctly inform the public about science, using experts in their fields; and to ensure that scientific research is adequately supported in terms of public financing. Many politicians have signed the pledge, including [[Beppe Grillo]], founder of the [[Five Star Movement]], a party which has strong ties to the antivaccination movement.{{R|\"Pact\"|\"Symptoms\"|\"Grillo\"}}\n\n== Approach with antivaccination activists ==\nBurioni is known for his matter-of-fact approach when dealing with antivaccination activists. \"I don't mind being curt with those who spend five minutes on Google and want to teach me about virology, which I have studied for 35 years. Science is no democracy.\" His stance on vaccinations has led to death threats against both himself and his daughter.{{R|\"Curt\"}}\n\n== Response to COVID-19 (Coronavirus) ==\nIn early February 2020, Burioni noted that the [[coronavirus]] was far more dangerous than the common flu and that due to its highly contagious nature, it was important not to underestimate it, but rather deal with it decisively. He further noted the importance of diagnosing cases as quickly as possible and isolating people who were or might get infected.{{R|\"underestimate\"|\"pop\"}} This position led to Burioni being accused of being a fascist and a supporter of the League, a far-right political party.{{R|\"accused\"}} Later the same month, Burioni again emphasised the importance of self-isolation and avoiding crowded places, noting that Italy had so far been unable to limit the rapid spread of the virus.{{R|\"draconian\"}} Burioni has backed the measures taken by the Italian government to halt the spread of [[COVID-19]], calling it an \"indispensable measure\".{{R|\"pop\"|\"indispensable\"}} Due to the Coronavirus outbreak, Burioni released his latest book, ''Virus. La grande sfida'' (''Virus. The Great Challenge'') in March 2020, several months earlier than originally planned. He received criticism on social media for doing this but responded saying that books on the epidemic were needed now in order to help people understand what was happening.{{R|\"Rush\"|\"Virus\"}} In response to the Italian government's plans to relax [[lockdown]] measures from May 4, Burioni said that anyone leaving their homes should be required to wear a mask and have some form of [[contact tracing]]. He further suggested that anyone found to have the virus should be isolated at a hotel or other facility rather than their home, warning that without these measures the virus could spread anew, resulting in having to start the lockdown all over again.{{R|\"tightrope\"}}\n\n==Awards and recognitions==\n*Jano Planco d'Oro Award, December 2017 in [[Rimini]], awarded annually to doctors, dentists, researchers, other health professionals, bodies, associations, or to other persons who have brought prestige to health, promoting the ethical principles of medicine.{{R|\"JanoPlanco\"}}\n*Annual Prize for Medicine of the UNAMSI, National Scientific Medical Union of Information, 11 December 2017.{{R|\"Unamsi\"}}\n*[[Isaac Asimov Awards|Premio Asimov]]. The essay 'The vaccine is not an opinion' won the Gran Sasso Science Institute of L'Aquila 2017 Asimov Award for scientific popularization.{{R|\"ResearchItaly\"}}\n*Internet Revelation Character of the Year Award at the Macchianera Internet Awards, the Italian Oscars of the Net, September 2017.{{R|\"Macchianera\"}}\n*Favignana Award - Florio Festival, 16 June 2018.{{R|\"Favignana\"}}\n*Ape d'Oro - Award of the Municipality of [[Segrate]], Milan, September 2018.{{R|\"Segrate\"}}\n*Best Character of the Year Award and Best Disclosure Site, Macchianera Internet Awards, the Italian Oscars of the Network, November 2018.{{R|\"Disclosure\"}}\n*Champion of Science Prize, Oscars of Goodness of the City Angels, Milan, January 2019.{{R|\"Goodness\"|\"Champion\"}}\n*Evidence Award 2019, GIMBE Foundation, [[Bologna]], March 2019.{{R|\"EvidencePrize\"}}\n*Picenum prize of the Pio Sodalizio dei Piceni Foundation, Rome, June 2019{{R|\"Picenum\"}}\n\n==Books==\n*{{cite book |author1=Donnici, Rocco |author2=Burioni, Roberto |author3=Marinelli, Massimiliano |title=Genetica. Valore delle biodiversit\u00e0. Sfida della bioingegneria (Genetics. Value of biodiversity. Bioengineering challenge) |publisher=Quattroventi |isbn=9788839204615 |language=it}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Burioni |first1=Roberto |title=Il vaccino non \u00e8 un'opinione: le vaccinazioni spiegate a chi proprio non le vuole capire (The vaccine is not an opinion: Vaccinations explained to those who just don't want to understand them) |publisher=Mondadori |isbn=978-8804684633 |language=it}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Burioni |first1=Roberto |title=La congiura dei somari: Perch\u00e9 la scienza non pu\u00f2 essere democratica (The conspiracy of dunces: Why science cannot be democratic) |publisher=Rizzoli |isbn=978-8817104609 |language=it}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Burioni |first1=Roberto |title=Balle mortali: Meglio vivere con la scienza che morire coi ciarlatani (Deadly lies: Better to live with science than to die with charlatans) |publisher=Rizzoli |isbn=978-8817105088 |language=it}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Burioni |first1=Roberto |title=Omeopatia: Bugie, leggende e verit\u00e0 (Homeopathy: Lies, legends and truths) |publisher=Rizzoli |isbn=978-8817141222 |language=it}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Burioni |first1=Roberto |title=Virus. La grande sfida (Virus. The Great Challenge) |publisher=Rizzoli |language=it}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"History\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.unisr.it/k-teacher/burioni-roberto/#1456764371925-7f163819-e2f9|title=Burioni Roberto - Universit\u00e0 Vita-Salute San Raffaele|last=|first=|date=|website=unisr.it|publisher=|language=|access-date=2016-09-25}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ScienceMag\">{{cite web |last1=Starr |first1=Douglas |title=This Italian scientist has become a celebrity by fighting vaccine skeptics |url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2020/01/italian-scientist-has-become-celebrity-fighting-vaccine-skeptics |website=ScienceMag |accessdate=20 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MedicalFacts\">{{cite web |title=Medical Facts |url=https://www.medicalfacts.it |accessdate=20 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Pact\">{{cite web |title=A Transversal Pact For Science |url=https://www.pattoperlascienza.it/2019/01/14/a-transversal-pact-for-science/ |website=pattoperlascienza |accessdate=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Symptoms\">{{cite web |last1=Broder |first1=David |title=The deadly symptoms of Italy\u2019s anti-vaccination movement |url=https://www.newstatesman.com/world/2019/02/deadly-symptoms-italy-s-anti-vaccination-movement |website=New Statesman |accessdate=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Grillo\">{{cite web |title=Vaccini, Grillo e Renzi firmano il Patto trasversale per la Scienza promosso da Burioni |url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/vaccini-grillo-e-renzi-firmano-il-patto-trasversale-per-la-scienza-promosso-da-burioni_3184744-201902a.shtml |website=tgcom24.mediaset.it |accessdate=22 January 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"FalseBalance\">{{cite web |last1=Villa |first1=Roberta |title=Vaccines: A case s