memory_card     = [[Secure Digital|microSD]] (supports up to 32&nbsp;GB)\n| battery         = 1200&nbsp;[[Ampere-hour|mAh]] [[Lithium-ion battery|Li-ion]] <br />User replaceable\n| input           = Multi-touch, capacitive [[touchscreen]] <br />[[A-GPS]] <br />[[Push button]]s\n| display         = [[TFT LCD]] 3.14\", 127 [[Pixel density|ppi]], <br />240\u00d7320 pixels QVGA, 256k colors\n| rear_camera     = 3.15-megapixel\n| media_formats = '''Audio'''b MP3, AAC, AAC+, eAAC+ <br /> '''Video''' MP4, H.264, H.263, Other formats supported through Apps\n| ringtone        = Vibration, MP3, WAV\n| connectivity    = 3.5&nbsp;mm [[TRS connector|jack]] <br />[[Bluetooth|Bluetooth v2.1]] with [[A2DP]] <br /> \n[[FM broadcasting|FM Radio]] with [[Radio Data System|RDS]]: <br />\n&nbsp;- mono (GT-S5570);  <br /> &nbsp;- stereo (GT-S5570i) <br />\nmicro [[USB 2.0]] <br />\n[[Wi-Fi]] [[802.11|802.11 (b/g/n)]]\n| other           = [[Swype]] keyboard\n| users           = Sujay\n| sar             = 0.961&nbsp;W/kg\n| predecessor     = [[Samsung Galaxy 5]]\n| successor       = [[Samsung Galaxy Mini 2]]\n}}\n[[File:Samsung_galaxy_mini.png|thumb|Samsung Galaxy Mini running [[Android Gingerbread|Android 2.3 Gingerbread]] ]]\nThe '''Samsung Galaxy Mini''' (GT-S5570[B/L/i]) is a [[smartphone]] manufactured by [[Samsung]] that runs the [[Android (operating system)|Android]] operating system. It was announced and released by Samsung in early 2011. In some markets it is known as '''Samsung Galaxy Next/Pop/NG'''\nIt is currently available in four different colors; steel grey, white, lime and orange. The same device is sold in the United States as the '''Samsung Dart''' exclusively for [[T-Mobile]]. The face buttons were changed to capacitive matching the rest of the Galaxy lineup.\n\nIt was succeeded by the [[Samsung Galaxy Mini 2]], featuring better screen (480x320 high contrast type vs old 320x240), higher clocked processor (600 >> 800 MHz) & drastically improved memory (278 >> 384 MB of RAM; 160 >> 1830 MB of internal storage avail.) over the original, as well as [[Bluetooth]] v3.0, [[Wi-Fi Direct]] & [[Near-field communication|NFC]] support, amongst others.\n\n==Features==\nThe Galaxy Mini is a 3.5G smartphone that offers quad-band [[GSM]] and was announced with two-band [[HSDPA]] (900/2100&nbsp;MHz) at 7.2&nbsp;Mbit/s. \nThe display is a {{convert|3.14|in|abbr=on}}-diagonal TFT LCD with a 240\u00d7320 pixels QVGA resolution supporting up to 256,000 colors.\n\nThe Galaxy Mini is presented as an entry-level smartphone, and is (as of 13 May 2011) one of the cheapest Android phones on the market.{{Citation needed|date=June 2013}}\n\nThe Galaxy Mini originally ran on [[Android Froyo|Android 2.2 \"Froyo\"]], but in May 2011, Samsung announced that the Galaxy Mini (along with other Galaxy models) will get an official upgrade to [[Android Gingerbread|Android 2.3 Gingerbread]]. An official upgrade to Android 2.3.6 (Gingerbread) was released via [[Samsung Kies]] on December 9, 2011 for some mobile operators. The Galaxy Mini can also be flashed with custom ROMs such as [[CyanogenMod]] releases (although not officially supported by Samsung) where it is codenamed ''tass''. The officially supported version of CyanogenMod on the Galaxy Mini as of August 2012 is CyanogenMod 7.2. It will run CyanogenMod 10/10.1/10.2 and even 11 but it is unofficially supported so there may be stability or performance issues, esp. in latter case.\nIt can be overclocked to 800&nbsp;MHz with SetCPU.\n\n===Key features===\n* Dual-touch (two fingers)\n* Quad-Band GSM and dual-band 3G support\n* 7.2&nbsp;Mbit/s [[HSDPA]]\n* [[WiFi]] 802.11 (b/g/n)\n* [[Bluetooth]] technology v 2.1\n* USB 2.0 (High Speed)\n* {{convert|3.14|in|mm|abbr=on}} 256K-color QVGA TFT touchscreen\n* [[ARM architecture#ARM cores|ARMv6]] 600&nbsp;MHz processor, 384&nbsp;MB RAM (279&nbsp;MB RAM available)\n* Adreno 200 [[GPU]]\n* Android OS v2.2 (Froyo)<ref>http://www.trustedreviews.com/samsung-galaxy-mini_Mobile-Phone_review</ref> with TouchWiz v3.0 UI, upgrade to v2.3.6 (Gingerbread) available in some places.\n* 160&nbsp;MB internal storage, hot-swappable [[MicroSD]] slot, 2&nbsp;GB card included\n* 3.15&nbsp;Mpixel fixed-focus camera with geo-tagging\n* [[GPS]] receiver with A-GPS\n* FM radio with RDS and Radio Text (not available in \"Dart\" version.)\n* 3.5&nbsp;mm audio jack\n* Document editor\n* Accelerometer and [[proximity sensor]]\n* [[Swype]] virtual keyboard\n* [[MicroUSB]] port (charging and data transfer) and stereo Bluetooth 2.1\n* SNS ([[social networking service]]) integration\n* Image/video editor\n\n==See also==\n*[[Galaxy Nexus]]\n*[[Samsung i5500|Galaxy Europa]] (2011)\n*[[Samsung Dart]] is alleged<ref>http://www.phonearena.com/phones/Samsung-Dart_id5542</ref> to be the same phone for the US T-Mobile market.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.samsung.com/galaxyace/mini_overview.html}}\n\n{{Samsung smartphone}}\n{{Samsung phones}}\n{{Android smartphones}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}}\n\n[[Category:Android (operating system) devices]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones introduced in 2011]]\n[[Category:Samsung mobile phones|Galaxy Mini]]\n[[Category:Samsung Galaxy|Galaxy Mini]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox Mobile phone\n| name            = Samsung Galaxy Mini <br /> GT-S5570, GT-S5570B, GT-S5570L, GT-S5570I\n| logo            = \n| logosize        = 150px <!-- include \"px\" - defaults to 250px if omitted -->\n| image           = File:Samsung Galaxy Mini.JPG\n| imagesize       = \n| manufacturer    = [[Samsung Electronics]]\n| series          = Galaxy\n| networks        = '''GSM''' 850&nbsp;MHz/900&nbsp;MHz/1800&nbsp;MHz/1900&nbsp;MHz <br /> '''HSDPA''' 7.2&nbsp;Mbit/s 850&nbsp;MHz / 900&nbsp;MHz / 1700&nbsp;MHz / 1900&nbsp;MHz / 2100&nbsp;MHz <br />'''CDMA''' [[CDMA2000 1xRTT]]/[[cdmaOne]]/[[Evolution-Data Optimized#EV-DO Rel. 0 (TIA-856 Release 0)|EV-DO Rel. 0]] 800&nbsp;MHz (SCH-i559)\n|announced        = January 2011\n| released        = February 2011\n| type            = [[Smartphone]]\n| form            = Slate\n| size            = {{convert|110.4|mm|in|abbr=on}}&nbsp;H<br />{{convert|60.6|mm|in|abbr=on}}&nbsp;W<br />{{convert|12.1|mm|in|abbr=on}}&nbsp;D<ref>[http://www.samsung.com/uk/consumer/mobile-devices/smartphones/android/GT-S5570EGAXEU-spec Galaxy Mini] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130105124822/http://www.samsung.com/uk/consumer/mobile-devices/smartphones/android/GT-S5570EGAXEU-spec |date=5 January 2013 }}</ref>\n| weight          = {{convert|106.6|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| os              = '''Original:''' [[Android (operating system)|Android]] [[Android Froyo|2.2 \"Froyo\"]] <br />'''Current:''' [[Android Gingerbread|Android 2.3.6 \"Gingerbread\"]] <br />'''Unofficial:''' [[Android KitKat|Android 4.4.4 \"KitKat\"]] via [[CyanogenMod]] 11\n| cpu             = Qualcomm MSM7227 600&nbsp;MHz (GT-S5570) <br />\nBroadcom BCM21553 832&nbsp;MHz (GT-S5570i)\n| gpu             = Adreno 200 (GT-S5570) <br />\nBroadcom BCM2763 Videocore IV (GT-S5570i)\n| memory          = 278&nbsp;MB (GT-S5570) <br />\n384&nbsp;MB (GT-S5570i)\n| storage         = 160&nbsp;MB\n| memory_card     = [[Secure Digital|microSD]] (supports up to 32&nbsp;GB)\n| battery         = 1200&nbsp;[[Ampere-hour|mAh]] [[Lithium-ion battery|Li-ion]] <br />User replaceable\n| input           = Multi-touch, capacitive [[touchscreen]] <br />[[A-GPS]] <br />[[Push button]]s\n| display         = [[TFT LCD]] 3.14\", 127 [[Pixel density|ppi]], <br />240\u00d7320 pixels QVGA, 256k colors\n| rear_camera     = 3.15-megapixel\n| media_formats = '''Audio'''b MP3, AAC, AAC+, eAAC+ <br /> '''Video''' MP4, H.264, H.263, Other formats supported through Apps\n| ringtone        = Vibration, MP3, WAV\n| connectivity    = 3.5&nbsp;mm [[TRS connector|jack]] <br />[[Bluetooth|Bluetooth v2.1]] with [[A2DP]] <br /> \n[[FM broadcasting|FM Radio]] with [[Radio Data System|RDS]]: <br />\n&nbsp;- mono (GT-S5570);  <br /> &nbsp;- stereo (GT-S5570i) <br />\nmicro [[USB 2.0]] <br />\n[[Wi-Fi]] [[802.11|802.11 (b/g/n)]]\n| other           = [[Swype]] keyboard\n| users           = Sujay\n| sar             = 0.961&nbsp;W/kg\n| predecessor     = [[Samsung Galaxy 5]]\n| successor       = [[Samsung Galaxy Mini 2]]\n}}\n[[File:Samsung_galaxy_mini.png|thumb|Samsung Galaxy Mini running [[Android Gingerbread|Android 2.3 Gingerbread]] ]]\nThe '''Samsung Galaxy Mini''' (GT-S5570[B/L/i]) is a [[smartphone]] manufactured by [[Samsung]] that runs the [[Android (operating system)|Android]] operating system. It was announced and released by Samsung in early 2011. In some markets it is known as '''Samsung Galaxy Next/Pop/NG'''\nIt is currently available in four different colors; steel grey, white, lime and orange. The same device is sold in the United States as the '''Samsung Dart''' exclusively for [[T-Mobile]]. The face buttons were changed to capacitive matching the rest of the Galaxy lineup.\n\nIt was succeeded by the [[Samsung Galaxy Mini 2]], featuring better screen (480x320 high contrast type vs old 320x240), higher clocked processor (600 >> 800 MHz) & drastically improved memory (278 >> 384 MB of RAM; 160 >> 1830 MB of internal storage avail.) over the original, as well as [[Bluetooth]] v3.0, [[Wi-Fi Direct]] & [[NFC]] support, amongst others.\n\n==Features==\nThe Galaxy Mini is a 3.5G smartphone that offers quad-band [[GSM]] and was announced with two-band [[HSDPA]] (900/2100&nbsp;MHz) at 7.2&nbsp;Mbit/s. \nThe display is a {{convert|3.14|in|abbr=on}}-diagonal TFT LCD with a 240\u00d7320 pixels QVGA resolution supporting up to 256,000 colors.\n\nThe Galaxy Mini is presented as an entry-level smartphone, and is (as of 13 May 2011) one of the cheapest Android phones on the market.{{Citation needed|date=June 2013}}\n\nThe Galaxy Mini originally ran on [[Android Froyo|Android 2.2 \"Froyo\"]], but in May 2011, Samsung announced that the Galaxy Mini (along with other Galaxy models) will get an official upgrade to [[Android Gingerbread|Android 2.3 Gingerbread]]. An official upgrade to Android 2.3.6 (Gingerbread) was released via [[Samsung Kies]] on December 9, 2011 for some mobile operators. The Galaxy Mini can also be flashed with custom ROMs such as [[CyanogenMod]] releases (although not officially supported by Samsung) where it is codenamed ''tass''. The officially supported version of CyanogenMod on the Galaxy Mini as of August 2012 is CyanogenMod 7.2. It will run CyanogenMod 10/10.1/10.2 and even 11 but it is unofficially supported so there may be stability or performance issues, esp. in latter case.\nIt can be overclocked to 800&nbsp;MHz with SetCPU.\n\n===Key features===\n* Dual-touch (two fingers)\n* Quad-Band GSM and dual-band 3G support\n* 7.2&nbsp;Mbit/s [[HSDPA]]\n* [[WiFi]] 802.11 (b/g/n)\n* [[Bluetooth]] technology v 2.1\n* USB 2.0 (High Speed)\n* {{convert|3.14|in|mm|abbr=on}} 256K-color QVGA TFT touchscreen\n* [[ARM architecture#ARM cores|ARMv6]] 600&nbsp;MHz processor, 384&nbsp;MB RAM (279&nbsp;MB RAM available)\n* Adreno 200 [[GPU]]\n* Android OS v2.2 (Froyo)<ref>http://www.trustedreviews.com/samsung-galaxy-mini_Mobile-Phone_review</ref> with TouchWiz v3.0 UI, upgrade to v2.3.6 (Gingerbread) available in some places.\n* 160&nbsp;MB internal storage, hot-swappable [[MicroSD]] slot, 2&nbsp;GB card included\n* 3.15&nbsp;Mpixel fixed-focus camera with geo-tagging\n* [[GPS]] receiver with A-GPS\n* FM radio with RDS and Radio Text (not available in \"Dart\" version.)\n* 3.5&nbsp;mm audio jack\n* Document editor\n* Accelerometer and [[proximity sensor]]\n* [[Swype]] virtual keyboard\n* [[MicroUSB]] port (charging and data transfer) and stereo Bluetooth 2.1\n* SNS ([[social networking service]]) integration\n* Image/video editor\n\n==See also==\n*[[Galaxy Nexus]]\n*[[Samsung i5500|Galaxy Europa]] (2011)\n*[[Samsung Dart]] is alleged<ref>http://www.phonearena.com/phones/Samsung-Dart_id5542</ref> to be the same phone for the US T-Mobile market.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.samsung.com/galaxyace/mini_overview.html}}\n\n{{Samsung smartphone}}\n{{Samsung phones}}\n{{Android smartphones}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}}\n\n[[Category:Android (operating system) devices]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones introduced in 2011]]\n[[Category:Samsung mobile phones|Galaxy Mini]]\n[[Category:Samsung Galaxy|Galaxy Mini]]\n", "name_user": "Cnwilliams", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:NFC\u2192Near-field communication", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samsung_Galaxy_Mini"}
